<h2>JavaScript String Methods</h2>

<p>The substr() method extract a part of a string
and returns the extracted parts in a new string:</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
let str = "Apple, Banana, Kiwi";
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = str.substr(-12,2);

</script>

</body>
</html>

(7,6) 7 is starting index, 6 is the length. count from 0. length can not be negative
